288","1190":"1190","1223":"1223","15 Jul 1262":"15 July 1262","10 Mar 1288":"10 March 1288","1288":"1288","1222":"1222","1241":"1241","1262":"1262","about 1241":"about 1241","Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Ashenfield Manor, Waltham, Canterbury, New Zealand":"Waltham, Canterbury, New Zealand","nameMeanings":[{"name":"deLacy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan.","English (East Yorkshire): of Norman origin, a habitational name for someone from Lassy in Calvados, France (see   Lacy  ), with the preposition <i>de</i> ‘from’."],"variants":[{"name":"Delacey","meanings":["English (East Yorkshire): of Norman origin, a variant of   Delacy  ."]},{"name":"Lacy","meanings":["English and Irish (of Norman origin): habitational name from Lassy in Calvados, named from a Gaulish personal name <i>Lascius</i> (of uncertain origin and meaning) + the locative suffix <i>-acum</i>."]}]},{"name":"Maud","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Medieval vernacular form of   Matilda .  This form was characteristically Low German (i.e. including medieval Dutch and Flemish). The wife of  William the Conqueror , who bore this name, was the daughter of  Baldwin , Count of Flanders. In Flemish and Dutch the letter <i>-t-</i> was generally lost when it occurred between vowels, giving forms such as <i>Ma(h)auld</i>. <i>Maud</i> or <i>Matilda</i> was also the name of the daughter (  1102–67 ) of  Henry I  of England; she was married early in life to the Holy Roman Emperor  Henry V , and later disputed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maud deLacy was born in 1223, in Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Richard IV Earl Gloucs HertsClare DeClare. She died on 10 March 1288, in her hometown, at the age of 65."},"et":{"1223–10 Mar 1288":"1223–10. märts 1288","1222–1262":"1222–1262","1190–1241":"1190–1241","1223–1288":"1223–1288","1190":"1190","1223":"1223","15 Jul 1262":"15. juuli 1262","10 Mar 1288":"10. märts 1288","1288":"1288","1222":"1222","1241":"1241","1262":"1262","about 1241":"umbes 1241","Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincoln, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Ashenfield Manor, Waltham, Canterbury, New Zealand":"Waltham, Canterbury, Uus-Meremaa"},"fi":{"1223–10 Mar 1288":"1223–10. maaliskuuta 1288","1222–1262":"1222–1262","1190–1241":"1190–1241","1223–1288":"1223–1288","1190":"1190","1223":"1223","15 Jul 1262":"15. heinäkuuta 1262","10 Mar 1288":"10. maaliskuuta 1288","1288":"1288","1222":"1222","1241":"1241","1262":"1262","about 1241":"noin 1241","Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincoln, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Ashenfield Manor, Waltham, Canterbury, New Zealand":"Waltham, Canterbury, Uusi-Seelanti"},"fr":{"1223–10 Mar 1288":"1223–10 mars 1288","1222–1262":"1222–1262","1190–1241":"1190–1241","1223–1288":"1223–1288","1190":"1190","1223":"1223","15 Jul 1262":"15 juillet 1262","10 Mar 1288":"10 mars 1288","1288":"1288","1222":"1222","1241":"1241","1262":"1262","about 1241":"environ 1241","Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincoln, Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre","Ashenfield Manor, Waltham, Canterbury, New Zealand":"Waltham, Canterbury, Nouvelle-Zélande","lifeSummary":"Maud deLacy est née en 1223, à Lincoln, Lincolnshire, Angleterre,